text: Ena Taslidža (born 14 August 2001) is a Bosnian footballer who plays as a midfielder and has appeared for the Bosnia and Herzegovina women's national team. ==Career== Taslidža has been capped for the Bosnia and Herzegovina national team, appearing for the team during the 2019 FIFA Women's World Cup qualifying cycle. ==References== ==External links== * * * Category:2001 births Category:Living people Category:Bosnia and Herzegovina women's footballers Category:Bosnia and Herzegovina women's international footballers Category:Women's association football midfielders
